docs.abstract: Jack Dorsey of Twitter and Marc Benioff of Salesforce, among others, are sparring over a Nov. 6 ballot initiative that would impose new corporate taxes.
docs.snippet: Jack Dorsey of Twitter and Marc Benioff of Salesforce, among others, are sparring over a Nov. 6 ballot initiative that would impose new corporate taxes.
docs.lead_paragraph: For months, technology companies in San Francisco have fought a local ballot proposition that would impose taxes on corporations to fund initiatives to help the homeless.

headline.main: In Liberal San Francisco, Tech Leaders Brawl Over Tax Proposal to Aid Homeless
headline.print_headline: A Battle Brews Between Moguls On Homeless Aid In San Francisco

docs.abstract: The Trump administration’s corporate tax cuts are unlikely to have their promised effect on job creation, a trio of prominent economists has concluded.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration’s corporate tax cuts are unlikely to have their promised effect on job creation, a trio of prominent economists has concluded.
docs.lead_paragraph: The new corporate tax cuts are unlikely to stimulate the level of job creation and wage growth that the Trump administration has promised, a trio of prominent economists has concluded, because high tax rates were not pushing much investment out of the United States in the first place.

headline.main: Tax Havens Blunt Impact of Corporate Tax Cut, Economists Say
headline.print_headline: How Tax Havens Override Tax Cuts

docs.abstract: The differing benefits by race reflect longstanding patterns of economic inequality and the structure of the law President Trump signed last year.
docs.snippet: The differing benefits by race reflect longstanding patterns of economic inequality and the structure of the law President Trump signed last year.
docs.lead_paragraph: The tax cuts that President Trump signed into law last year are disproportionately helping white Americans over African-Americans and Latinos, a disparity that reflects longstanding racial economic inequality in the United States and the choices that Republicans made in crafting the law.

headline.main: White Americans Gain the Most From Trump’s Tax Cuts, a Report Finds
headline.print_headline: White Americans Gain the Most From Trump’s Tax Cuts, a Report Finds

docs.abstract: The first round of the Fed’s annual stress tests found banks are prepared to withstand a downturn, which could presage big shareholder payouts next week.
docs.snippet: The first round of the Fed’s annual stress tests found banks are prepared to withstand a downturn, which could presage big shareholder payouts next week.
docs.lead_paragraph: The nation’s biggest banks are strong enough to continue lending if the economy plunges into a severe downturn, an assessment by the Federal Reserve on Thursday that could fuel Wall Street’s calls to further relax financial regulations.

headline.main: Biggest Banks Pass Fed’s Stress Tests
headline.print_headline: Biggest Banks  Easily Pass  Fed Stress Test
